State v. Thomas Howard, alias William Clark. (November 17, 1931.)

Pennewill, C. J., Harrington and Richards, J. J., sitting.

*144Reuben Satterthwaite, Attorney-General, Charles F. Richards and David J. Reinhardt, Jr., Deputy Attorneys-General, for the State. Ellwood F. Melson and Louis L. Redding for the de- • fendant. Court of Oyer and Terminer for New Castle County,

November Term, 1931.

Indictment for rape,

No. 74,

November Term, 1931.

*145Pennewill, C. J.:

The contention of the defendant’s

attorney may be in conformity with the trend of recent authority; but we cannot disregard a decision in our own state which seems to be directly in point. State v. Turner, Housh Cr. Cas. 76.

The objection of the State is, therefore, sustained.
